From bcfa66f4a1fb196d19002a51c9ca5cecbf03d5a2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.local>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 14:16:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Make 'Verify connection' actually verify against Meta

Previously this only checked that username/business ID/token fields
were non-empty and would happily report success on completely fake
input - a real bug, not just a documentation gap. It now calls
graph.instagram.com/me with the token and only reports connected if
Meta accepts it, overwriting username/business ID with whatever Meta
actually returns (rather than trusting typed values). The settings
form also now shows an explicit pass/fail message instead of only
relying on the connected badge.
---
 .../settings/components/settings-form.tsx     | 17 +++++++++
 .../repositories/settings-repository.ts       | 27 ++++++++++++--
 .../settings/services/settings-service.ts     | 36 ++++++++++++++-----
 3 files changed, 70 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/features/settings/components/settings-form.tsx b/src/features/settings/components/settings-form.tsx
